      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_2",
      "text": "High cortisol exerts its effects through glucocorticoid receptors and mineralocorticoid receptors in the hippocampus, mediating neurophysiological responses. Prolonged activation may lead to neuronal damage, reduced neuroplasticity, and cognitive impairment.",
